  <original-body>The main reason for using `&lt;button&gt;` (instead of `&lt;input type=&quot;submit&quot;&gt;` et al) is to make a button with content that is formatted, or different from the button's `value`, or both. The current version of `button_tag` doesn't support this very well, because it defaults `type` to `&quot;button&quot;` and doesn't let you pass a block.

Attached are patches for both of these issues; alternatively, there's a [pull request](https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/189).</original-body>
